{
	"name": "Avatar of Ash",
	"type": "feature",
	"img": "icons/creatures/magical/spirit-fire-orange.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": "<p>At 18th level, you can invoke the true power of your fiery blood. As a bonus action, you can ignite yourself for 1 minute. During this time:</p><ul><li><p>You gain a flying speed (hover) equal to your walking speed.</p></li><li><p>You are immune to fire damage, and you ignore resistances to fire damage enemy may have, and creatures immune to fire are only resistant to your fire damage.</p></li><li><p>Once per turn, when you deal fire or radiant damage to a creature, you can choose to cause that creature to burn with mythic fire: At the start of its next turn, it takes additional damage equal to your Charisma modifier, and must succeed on a Constitution saving throw (Spell save DC) or be [[/condition id=blinded]] until the end of that turn.</p></li><li><p>When you cast a spell that deals fire damage, you can reroll any damage die with a result of 1, you must take the new result.</p></li></ul><p>You can use this feature once per long rest, or by spending 5 sorcery points.</p>",
